list.item:
III. Nine dot asterisks, connected with lines
                                   (e.g. fols.: 25ra, l.33; 36vb, l.38; 59vb, l.24; 118vb,
                                   l.22);

chain of black lines and red and black dots
                                   (e.g. fols.: 9vb, l.12; 25ra, 18,
                                   23; 35ra, l.1; 41ra, l.7; 96ra, l.1);

chain of coronis signs, between a chain of
                                   double black lines and nine dot asterisks, and a chain of black
                                   lines and dots (esp. 59vb);

handDesc.handNote:
- ጵ has the 6th order marker set up on
                       the vertical stroke at the top, oriented to the left (e.g., 19vb
                       l.22);

- ሎ has sometimes the 7th order marker
                       attached directly at the body of the letter, without horizontal stroke
                       (e.g., 14ra l.8);

- ፮ is with the loop open, looking
                       like “compressed” ፯ (e.g., 84vb
                       l.22);
